{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9b4f143a-7d76-4ef4-a738-3d651494f3e5","content":"**MSTest.Sdk 4.x dropped the VSTest compatibility bridge.**\n\nIn 3.x, the SDK included a VSTest adapter bridge by default (via `EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatformVSTestBridge`), so `vstest.console` could still discover and run tests. In 4.x, that bridge was removed — the test project is now a standalone executable using **Microsoft.Testing.Platform** only.\n\n**Fix:** Switch your CI from `vstest.console` to one of:\n\n1. **`dotnet test`** (recommended — supports Microsoft.Testing.Platform natively):\n   ```bash\n   dotnet test TestProject.csproj\n   ```\n\n2. **Run the test executable directly:**\n   ```bash\n   dotnet run --project TestProject.csproj\n   ```\n\nIf you temporarily need `vstest.console` support, you can try re-enabling the bridge in your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatformVSTestBridge>true</EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatformVSTestBridge>\n```\n\nbut this shim is deprecated and may be removed in future versions. Migrating your pipeline to `dotnet test` is the recommended long-term solution.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9909f36f-0367-45e5-a352-abe3232b79b2","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a known breaking change in MSTest.Sdk. Starting with MSTest.Sdk 3.x, MSTest moved to Microsoft.Testing.Platform as the default runner. In MSTest.Sdk 4.0+, the VSTest compatibility layer (the bridge/adapter that lets vstest.console discover and run tests) was removed by default.\n\nSpecifically, in MSTest.Sdk 3.x, the property `EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatformVSTestBridge` defaulted to `true`, which included the VSTest adapter bridge so that vstest.console could still discover tests. In MSTest.Sdk 4.x, this bridge is no longer included by default — the project only supports Microsoft.Testing.Platform runner natively.\n \nIf they're running tests with `vstest.console` in their CI pipeline, they'll need to either migrate to `dotnet test` (which natively supports Microsoft.Testing.Platform in .NET SDK 9+) or re-enable the VSTest bridge by setting the property back to `true` in their project file, though that option may not be available in 4.x.","outputTokens":782,"requestId":"0430:207FB7:1DCAA7A:21E6C2A:69E836C9"},"id":"a6587804-c655-4c9f-85a9-d9749cdef418","timestamp":"2026-04-22T02:47:52.681Z","parentId":"563d8349-f541-464f-814d-6360f7d7c670"}
